{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770220213,"nonce":"7a5k2T8h5iw9FGJrBKl5qK9ON7o=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87oSp69","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/162","origin":"github"},"title":"Improve workflow support for stacked PRs and sub-issues","message":"## Summary\n\nEnhance workflow tooling to better support the common pattern of sub-issues that create stacked PRs (PRs that branch from other PR branches instead of main).\n\n## Problem Statement\n\nWhen a PR review identifies issues requiring fixes (like #148 from PR #146 review), the current workflow has friction:\n\n**Current Experience:**\n1. Agent creates worktree for sub-issue from `main`\n2. File to fix doesn't exist on `main` (only in PR branch)\n3. User must manually tell agent to recreate from PR branch\n4. Agent deletes worktree, recreates from correct base\n\n**Root Cause:** `worktree_create.sh` defaults to creating branches from current HEAD, with no awareness of issue relationships or parent PRs.\n\n## Stacked PR Pattern\n\nThis pattern is very common:\n\n```\nmain\n  └── PR #146 (feature/issue-139)\n       └── PR #161 (feature/issue-148) - fixes bugs found in review\n```\n\n**Common scenarios:**\n- Code review findings → sub-PR to fix issues before merge\n- Test failures in PR → sub-PR to fix tests\n- Large feature split → multiple stacked PRs\n- Feature dependencies → stack B on A\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n\n### 1. Enhance `worktree_create.sh`\n\nAdd `--base-branch` parameter:\n\n```bash\n# Explicit base branch\n./worktree_create.sh --issue 148 --type workspace --base-branch feature/issue-139\n\n# Or interactive prompt when parent detected\n./worktree_create.sh --issue 148 --type workspace\n# ⚠️  Issue #148 is a sub-issue of #139\n# ℹ️  PR #146 exists for issue #139 on branch feature/issue-139\n# ? Create branch from feature/issue-139 instead of main? (Y/n)\n```\n\n**Implementation:**\n```bash\n# In worktree_create.sh\nwhile [[ $# -gt 0 ]]; do\n    case $1 in\n        --base-branch)\n            BASE_BRANCH=\"$2\"\n            shift 2\n            ;;\n        # ... existing options\n    esac\ndone\n\n# Use BASE_BRANCH if specified, otherwise default to main\nBASE_REF=\"${BASE_BRANCH:-main}\"\n```\n\n### 2. Auto-Detect Parent Issues\n\nParse issue body for parent references:\n\n```markdown\n## Parent Issue\nSub-issue of #139\n```\n\nScript logic:\n```bash\n# Extract parent issue from GitHub API\nPARENT_ISSUE=$(gh issue view $ISSUE --json body | jq -r '.body' | grep -oP 'Sub-issue of #\\K[0-9]+' || true)\n\nif [ -n \"$PARENT_ISSUE\" ]; then\n    # Check if parent has open PR\n    PARENT_PR=$(gh pr list --search \"#$PARENT_ISSUE\" --state open --json number,headRefName | jq -r '.[0].headRefName' || true)\n    \n    if [ -n \"$PARENT_PR\" ]; then\n        echo \"⚠️  Issue #$ISSUE is a sub-issue of #$PARENT_ISSUE\"\n        echo \"ℹ️  PR exists on branch $PARENT_PR\"\n        # Prompt or use as default\n    fi\nfi\n```\n\n### 3. Documentation\n\nAdd section to `.agent/AI_RULES.md` or `CONTRIBUTING.md`:\n\n```markdown\n## Working with Stacked PRs\n\nWhen a PR review creates sub-issues that must be fixed before merge:\n\n**1. Create Sub-Issue Worktree**\n```bash\n# Check if parent issue has PR\ngh pr list | grep \"#$PARENT_ISSUE\"\n\n# Create worktree from parent PR branch\ncd /path/to/workspace\ngit checkout feature/issue-$PARENT\n./worktree_create.sh --issue $SUB_ISSUE --type workspace\n# Or with explicit base:\n./worktree_create.sh --issue $SUB_ISSUE --type workspace --base-branch feature/issue-$PARENT\n```\n\n**2. Create Sub-PR Targeting Parent**\n```bash\ncd .workspace-worktrees/issue-$SUB_ISSUE\n# Make changes, commit\ngh pr create --base feature/issue-$PARENT --head feature/issue-$SUB\n```\n\n**3. After Sub-PR Merges**\n```bash\n# Update parent worktree\ncd .workspace-worktrees/issue-$PARENT\ngit pull origin feature/issue-$PARENT\n```\n```\n\nAdd to `.agent/AI_CLI_QUICKSTART.md`:\n\n```markdown\n### Creating Branches for Sub-Issues\n\n**Before creating a worktree:**\n1. Check if parent issue has an open PR:\n   `gh pr list | grep \"#$PARENT_ISSUE\"`\n2. If PR exists, note its branch name\n3. Checkout that branch before creating worktree:\n   `git checkout feature/issue-$PARENT`\n4. Then create worktree normally\n```\n\n### 4. Agent Instructions\n\nUpdate AI agent rules to check for parent PRs:\n\n```markdown\n## Rule: Check for Parent PRs Before Creating Worktree\n\nWhen creating a worktree for a sub-issue:\n\n1. Check issue body for \"Sub-issue of #N\" or \"Parent Issue\"\n2. If found, check if parent has open PR:\n   `gh pr list --search \"#N\" --state open`\n3. If PR exists, create branch from that PR's branch\n4. If no PR or unsure, ask user\n```\n\n## Tasks\n\n- [ ] Add `--base-branch` parameter to `worktree_create.sh`\n- [ ] Implement parent issue detection from GitHub API\n- [ ] Add interactive prompt when parent PR detected\n- [ ] Document stacked PR workflow in CONTRIBUTING.md\n- [ ] Add quick reference to AI_CLI_QUICKSTART.md\n- [ ] Update AI agent rules for sub-issue handling\n- [ ] Add examples to CLI_COMMANDS.md\n- [ ] Update worktree_create.sh usage/help text\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- ✅ `worktree_create.sh --base-branch \u003cbranch\u003e` creates worktree from specified branch\n- ✅ Script detects parent issues from GitHub and suggests base branch\n- ✅ Documentation clearly explains stacked PR workflow\n- ✅ AI agents know to check for parent PRs before creating worktrees\n- ✅ Help text includes examples of stacked PR usage\n\n## Benefits\n\n1. **Reduced Friction**: No more recreating worktrees from wrong branch\n2. **Clear Workflow**: Explicit pattern for handling PR review issues\n3. **AI-Friendly**: Agents can detect and handle stacked PRs automatically\n4. **Better DX**: Interactive prompts guide users to correct choices\n\n## Effort Estimate\n\n**Medium** (4-6 hours)\n- Script enhancement: 2 hours\n- Documentation: 2 hours\n- Testing: 1-2 hours\n\n## Priority\n\n**Medium** - Process improvement that reduces friction for common workflow\n\n---\n**🤖 Authored-By**: `Copilot CLI Agent`\n**🧠 Model**: `Claude Sonnet 4.5`","files":null}]}